            <bug_when>2011-11-02 11:50:48 +0100</bug_when>
            <thetext>If the assertion wrapping feature of the unit testing system is active (which is the default), the &quot;error&quot; state will be applied to unit tests with failing assertions. This state is supposed to be used for tests with general exceptions, &quot;failure&quot; would be the appropriate state.

This is not that big of a deal since the Testrunner views generally treat &quot;failure&quot; and &quot;error&quot; in the same way but it should nevertheless fixed for the sake of internal consistency.</thetext>
